#1 Resected grade 4/4 adenocarcinoma of the rectum, clinical stage T4, NX, M0
At the time of this dictation the final pathology report on the surgical specimen was still not available.  Mr. Como underwent induction chemotherapy and radiation for rectal cancer and is status-post resection.  I met with the patient and family members to discuss additional treatment options.  It is my recommendation for Mr. Como to be seen by his local oncologist in Great Mills in about four weeks from now to discuss additional chemotherapy (FOLFOX).  I briefly discussed with the patient that it is our recommendation for him to undergo four months of chemotherapy with a FOLFOX-based regimen.  Briefly discussed with the patient some of the side-effects associated with the use of chemotherapy in this setting.  Patient is to have a more detailed conversation regarding additional side-effects of the chemotherapy with his local oncologist.  I offered the patient the possibility of coming to El Monte Clinic for that follow-up.
Later...results of pathology shows 3 lymph nodes with tumor invasion and significant treatment effects. IHC for hMLH is negative for all markers. These results were communicated to the patient and family members.

[end section id="20112"]

